  "texts": [
    "(1) Weakly supervised and small sample detection: At this stage, the object detection model is trained by large-scale instance-labeled data, and data labeling is a timeconsuming and labor-intensive project.",
    "Weakly supervised object detection reduces the cost of data annotation and efficiently trains the network with a little quantity of annotated data.",
    "The labeled data can be transferred from related domains through transfer learning and then trained with a small amount of labeled data in the desired domain to improve object detection in the desired domain.",
    "(2) Multi-modal detection: To overcome the problem of monolithic data set categories, data from multiple modalities such as RGB images, 3D images, etc.",
    "can be fused, which is crucial for fields such as autonomous driving and intelligent robotics."
  ],
